 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sparkyzapmaster>Sparky Zapmaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(10/25/02 12:35:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wdwinfo.com/sites/bansheebluetwo/Penguins.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: comment</span><hr size=1> Disease, Innovation and Nightmare zone-ins are all safe in that nothing spawns right in that spot.  However, Innovation is a pain because it's a bit of a dead end there.  If someone runs a train to the zone, there's nowhere you can go to get safe.<br>
<br>
Disease is the relative easiest that I've found so far.  The flies hit for around 200 max, the &quot;weakest&quot; of any zone, so they're probably soloable for those of you who prefer it.  However, when we were out island hopping pulling skeeters, we kept having rats and larvae jump seemingly out of the ground at us, much like the skele and worm traps in Maiden's Eye.  They hit for 200-300 and could really put a damper on your soloing efforts.  As for the look of the zone, a friend of mine put it best: &quot;hairy tang.&quot;<br>
<br>
Innovation has the coolest looking mobs by far.  The way the golems hop in on one leg always makes me laugh.  The respawn there is fast as heck too, right around six minutes, so it's a great zone for a good group to grind away in.  The only problem is what I mentioned above: the dead end zone-in.  If you wipe farther in and are waiting for your corpses to come to the graveyard, hope there's nobody running out.<br>
<br>
Nightmare is the coolest looking zone.  The sky made my jaw drop, the way it was black and purple and pulsating.  Absolutely beautiful.  It's a pretty dark zone too, matching the idea behind it.  Treants are the coolest mobs I saw in there, but those damn blood ravens are hard as hell to see and you can easily get one or two more on your puller as he comes back.  They're rootable (we had no mezzer), so crowd control wasn't that hard.<br>
<br>
The one thing I've noticed about all the planes is this: they're pretty unforgiving.  You can't really mess around with mobs that hit for 250+.  Unless you've got incredible gear, find a plate class to be your main tank.  Our 57 monk just could not cut it in Nightmare, but the 56 paladin worked just fine. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52766&quot;" target="_new">Sparky Zapmaster</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
